genresAdvancedInfo.name: chaabi algerien
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Chaabi algerien is a traditional Algerian music genre that originated in the 1920s. It is characterized by its upbeat tempo and the use of traditional instruments such as the mandolin, banjo, and accordion. The lyrics often focus on love, social issues, and daily life in Algeria.
